1: Object-Oriented Design

C++ has support for Class, object, inheritance, abstraction, etc as a result code reusability, 
data hiding, and memory management is possible
C doesn’t have OOPs features, data is open everywhere and move freely through functions

2: Procedural v/s Hybrid Language

C is a procedural language i.e development of code in the form of a list of  instructions (functions) 
where each instruction conveys the compiler to do some action
C++ is viewed as Hybrid language i.e it can be used as object-oriented or traditional C type Procedural Programming 
i.e using OOPS in C++ is optional, whereas in java it is mandatory.

3: Namespace Feature

C has predefined function support only in the form of header files, as a result, 
You cannot duplicate the names within the file or program
C++ has a namespace feature which enables having the same names for functions or variables, 
which  solves the naming collision problem
