C was developed by Dennis Ritchie in the 1970s at AT&T Bell Labs with the combined features  of BCPL and Basic Programming Languages
Inspired by the class feature of Simula67 and block-structured
Programming in C, C++was developed by Bjarne Stroustrup in 1979 as an extension of C.

